description:
The Torchlighters: The Martin Luther Story | Full Episode | Stephen Daltry | David Reggi | Robert Fernandez

Martin Luther didn’t mean to spark the Reformation with his 95 Theses, but his realization that salvation comes through faith and not works ignited the revolution that changed the world. As Pope Leo X hounds and fights him at every turn, will Luther have the courage to stand strong—even to death? Find out with the fifteenth episode of the Torchlighters, commemorating the 500th anniversary of the Reformation!

In a world ruled by the church, all it took was one little nail, one well-written scroll, and one sharp-tongued monk to turn everything upside-down! Martin Luther didn’t mean to spark the Reformation with his 95 Theses, but his realization that salvation comes through faith and not works ignited the revolution that changed the world. As Pope Leo X hounds and fights him at every turn, will Luther have the courage to stand strong—even to death? Find out with the fifteenth episode of the Torchlighters, commemorating the 500th anniversary of the Reformation!

The Torchlighters series is brought to you in partnership with The Voice of the Martyrs (VOM). VOM serves persecuted Christians living in the world’s most difficult and dangerous places to follow Christ. Learn more about their work at vom.org.

Director: Robert Fernandez
Starring: Stephen Daltry, David Reggi
